      • getDiscrepancies

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer> getDiscrepancies()
        Getter method for the discrepancy statistics of a query.
        Returns:
        the discrepancy statistics as a Map where the entry "key" corresponds to the total number of differences in the keys of a query, the entry "value" corresponds to the total number of differences in the values of a query, and the entry "ignored" corresponds to the total number of properties that were ignored by the QueryEngine.

      • generateInternalQueries

        public java.lang.String generateInternalQueries(java.lang.String path)
        Takes in a single path input and generates a series of queries between the subdirectories of the specified path.
        example path parameters:
        dev1/fabric2
        example queries:
        dev1/fabric2/node1
        dev1/fabric2/node2
        dev1/fabric2/node1
        dev1/fabric2/node3
        dev1/fabric2/node2
        dev1/fabric2/node3
        Parameters:
        path - the path containing the subdirectories being compared against each other
        Returns:
        a String representing the status of the query: null if successful, else error message
